review_blob: Some of the worst crap Ive tasted in a while. Overly sweet and unbalanced.

belgian strong ale with slight pink hue (pinot noir juice added).  slightly vegetal nose with coriander and hint of nuttiness.  high alcohol with vanilla, coriander, vegetative notes.  attack is medium dry with long finish and bitter hop in the mid palate.  NIce, definitely not worth the price.  Drink at 50-60F to get the most out of this.   

I always love the yeast strains that Dogfish uses, very unique.  No exception in this brew.

what else can be said?  This is the classic stout - rich, creamy.  Surprising non-filling.  Creamy head, roasted malt aroma.  Dry, almost burnt flavor with hints of chocolate, coffee.  Long finish.  Im not reporting anything new, but I always enjoy a good Guinness Draught.

(bottle) Pine tar on the nose was evident as soon as the cap came off.
Golden hue, off white head.  On the nose, pine tar that fades, citrus, fruit punch.  NIce, smooth palate.  The malt hides the overwhelming 93 IBUs well, IMO.  Pine, citrus. lupulin resin on the finish.  Nice IPA.

For a "grocery store" beer, you cant do much better than this.  The cascade flavoring hops and orange hue make me proud to be an American.  In fact, I risk tar and feather when I suggest that the stars of old glory should be replaced by cascade hop cones and her red stripes replaced by lines the same color as the amber hue of this beer.  Salute this beer and accept it as your national beverage, America.

beer_name: Dogfish Head Midas Touch Golden Elixir

review_blob:
Thick tan head, black viscous fluid.
Nose of soy sauce, smoke, oak and chocolate.
Sweet with hop bitterness on the attack, with espresso bean, vanilla, dark chocolate and ash.
beer_name: Santa Fe State Pen Imperial Porter

review_blob: Pours slightly hazy,, with rich golden color.  Impressive citrus flavors with a moderate, yet smooth, bitter finish.  This is a very dry beer without almost no sweet taste.  An excellent beer.

Deep black drink with hardly any light able to come through.  This beer has mocha colored head that persists and looks like rising yeast as it gets closer to the bottom of the glass.  Very smooth on the palate with sweet caramel and currant flavors.  It has amazingly deceptive high alcohol, as I would guess this to have about 7% if I didnt know better.  A little sweet for me, but otherwise an excellent stout.

Almost no head.  Caramel aroma with a hint of pear.   Dark brown color.    Not very sweet with a slightly bitter finish.  This beer has abv 6%; However, the alcohol comes through too much against the flavor, in my opinion. Still, a very drinkable and enjoyable bitter ale.

Warning, this beer is not for little girls or Boy Scouts.  

Rated on the first pour:  Off white, slightly yellow head.  Appealing crisp amber color, clear, no sediment.  The hops yield a potent and obvious citrus aroma.  Lingers on the palate with a nice bitter finish that should be typical of a DIPA.  Slight sweetness that was held back to appropriate levels.  I cant say enough about this beer.  They got this beer right.. Should take the enamel off your teeth.
Sweet malt, beet candy aroma.  This beer hides its high alcohol % well, at 9.2% its deceptively smooth.  My favorite trappist beer up to this point.
